  [6] The =E2=80=9CKeep it secret, keep it safe=E2=80=9D  quote is garbled =
a bit in the complaint by stray punctuation (which I have cleaned up), pres=
umably because he texted too fast.


  [7] I am eliding the details of what it means for crypto to be =E2=80=9Ct=
otally mainstream.=E2=80=9D Maybe it means that all dollars are on the bloc=
kchain, banks issue stablecoins, the Fed issues central bank digital curren=
cies, etc. The point here is that I think in any variation of that world yo=
u=E2=80=99re not keeping your dollars at Circle or Tether earning 0%.


  [8] The other problem is that keeping the money in regulated US banks was=
 not, this year, all *that* safe; some of Circle=E2=80=99s money was at Sil=
icon Valley Bank when it collapsed. Tether avoided that problem by keeping =
