<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One way to acquire a public company is, you pu=
t out a press release saying =E2=80=9CI am making a public offer to buy all=
 the shares of this company,=E2=80=9D and that press release starts a compl=
ex process in which the company=E2=80=99s board feels compelled to negotiat=
e a deal with you, or if they don=E2=80=99t then you follow through on the =
press release and launch a hostile tender offer for the shares. The press r=
elease is a key moment in the campaign, the point where you go public, but =
it is preceded by lots of preparation and followed by lots of tactical mane=
uvering. The acquisition of a public company is difficult and complex and t=
ypically requires many hours of work from hundreds of people to get everyth=
ing done.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The press release is easy, though? You can jus=
t type it? Business Wire seems to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/33377885.258417/aHR0cHM6Ly9zZXJ2aWNlcy5idXNpbmVzc3dpcmUuY29=
tL3ByaWNpbmc/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7ad7abc0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" item=
scope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorat=
ion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00000=
0; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> charge several hun=
dred dollars</a> for disseminating a press release, so it=E2=80=99s not=C2=
=A0<em>free</em>, but if you pay Business Wire=E2=80=99s fees=C2=A0it=E2=80=
=99ll be picked up pretty broadly and everyone will think that you are laun=
ching your effort to buy the company. And so if you want to=C2=A0<em>preten=
d=C2=A0</em>to acquire a public company, you can just do the press release =
and not all the other parts.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Why would you want to pretend to acquire a pub=
lic company? The standard reason is market manipulation:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You buy some stock in the company at =
a low price.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You put out a press r=
elease saying =E2=80=9CFake Capital Management LP is buying this company at=
 a 90% premium.=E2=80=9D</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">People an=
d/or algorithms read the press release and buy the stock to speculate on th=
e takeover.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You sell the stock at =
a high price.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We talk about this from <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33377885.258417/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21i=
ZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTUtMDYtMDQvZ3V5LXdoby1kaWQtYXZvbi1ob2F=
4LXdhcy10ZXJyaWJsZS1hdC1ob2F4ZXM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTExNTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX2=
1lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMTE1JnV0bV9jY=
W1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6f1fef0f" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> time</a=
> to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33377885.2584=
17/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTctMDUtMjIv=
Zml0Yml0LXF1YW50cy1hbmQtdWJlcj9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTE1MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWV=
kaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzExMTUmdXRtX2NhbX=
BhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB64a02fdc" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> time</a>.=
 I do not think it=E2=80=99s the=C2=A0<em>only=C2=A0</em>reason, though.<a =
class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transpar=
ent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0My impression is that there are people who just=C2=A0enjoy preten=
ding to buy public companies, as a sort of live-action fantasy business gam=
e.=C2=A0Elon Musk, for instance, occasionally <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/33377885.258417/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
vbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDctMDkvZWxvbi1zLW91dD9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTE1Mj=
NfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fd=
GVybT0yMzExMTUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcf0=
49715" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;"> pretends that he is going to buy public companies</a>, with=
out ever profiting from the price action: It is just a fun game for him, <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33377885.258417/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cuYnVzaW5lc3NpbnNpZGVyLmNvbS9lbG9uLW11c2stcGxheXMtc3RyYXRlZ3ktdml=
kZW8tZ2FtZS1iYXR0bGUtb2YtcG9seXRvcGlhLTIwMjMtMQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB02=
994855" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;"> like Polytopia</a>, except=C2=A0business conquest instead =
of military conquest. It is=C2=A0<em>incredibly=C2=A0</em>expensive: When h=
e pretended he was going to buy out Tesla Inc., he was fined $20 million by=
 the US Securities and Exchange Commission; when he pretended he was going =
to buy Twitter Inc., he was=C2=A0<em>forced to buy it=C2=A0</em>for $44 bil=
lion. It is possible that nobody in human history has ever spent more money=
 on a hobby than Elon Musk has spent on his hobby of pretending to buy publ=
ic companies. He must really enjoy it!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I find this very relatable.=C2=A0I remember re=
ading <em>Barbarians at the Gate=C2=A0</em>and thinking =E2=80=9Cthis just =
seems =E2=80=A6=C2=A0fun?=E2=80=9D and then, later, becoming a mergers-and-=
acquisitions lawyer and then an investment banker. That is one rather unima=
ginative=C2=A0approach. Another approach would be reading <em>Barbarians at=
 the=C2=A0Gate</em>, thinking it seemed fun, and then becoming a guy who pu=
ts out fake merger press releases.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway, a little after 5 p.m. on Friday, Nov. =
3, when WeWork Inc. was sliding into bankruptcy but not quite bankrupt yet =
(<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33377885.258417/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMDcvd2V3b3Jr=
LWdvZXMtYmFua3J1cHQtY2FwcGluZy1jby13b3JraW5nLWNvbXBhbnktcy1kb3duZmFsbD9jbXB=
pZD1CQkQxMTE1MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2=
xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzExMTUmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8=
524a319a23cBf5dfbadc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">it filed on Monday, Nov. 6</a>), a very fun p=
ress release came out on Business Wire.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"=
#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: n=
one !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-b=
lock;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>=C2=A0A sample:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A Proposal by Cole Capital Funds Seeks to Acqu=
ire 51% of all minority ownership shares of WeWork, Inc. for $9.00 per shar=
e in Cash</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Cole Capital Funds sent the following letter t=
o the Board of Directors of WeWork, Inc.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We believe that it is in the best interest of =
WeWork to support our acquisition of 51% of all the outstanding shares owne=
d by minority shareholders at a price of $9.00 per share and provide Cole w=
ith proper representation on the company board.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have consulted with God, legal, financial a=
nd other advisors to assist us with this transaction. We stand ready to pro=
ceed timely.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">See, when I was an M&amp;A lawyer, I wrote a l=
ot of press releases that were a bit like this, but in exactly none of them=
=C2=A0did I write =E2=80=9CWe have consulted with God.=E2=80=9D Not standar=
d in high-stakes public-company M&amp;A. But in fantasy M&amp;A, you can co=
nsult with whomever you want! Have fun! That=E2=80=99s why you=E2=80=99re d=
oing it, for fun!</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/33377885.258417/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2Fy=
dGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMTMvcmVhbC1lc3RhdGUtaW52ZXN0b3ItbGFybW9yZS1mYWNlcy1zZWM=
taW5xdWlyeS1vbi13ZXdvcmstb2ZmZXI_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTExNTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX2=
1lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMTE1JnV0bV9jY=
W1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2fa317d4" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Bloombe=
rg=E2=80=99s Patrick Clark reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A real estate investor facing scrutiny from le=
nders and investors is now the subject of a government inquiry into an offe=
r to buy shares in WeWork Inc.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The US Securities and Exchange Commission has =
sent inquiries to Jonathan Larmore, the founder of Arciterra Cos., about a =
Nov. 3 press release in which an entity called Cole Capital Funds said it w=
as seeking to buy shares in the coworking company at a significant premium,=
 according to a person familiar with the matter who asked not to be named c=
iting private information. The inquiry includes Larmore=E2=80=99s trading h=
istory in WeWork stock and options, the person said.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A company filing links Larmore to Cole Capital=
 Funds, which was registered in October with the Arizona Corporation Commis=
sion. The real estate investor was already facing an SEC inquiry about Arci=
terra, which had owned as many as 80 properties including strip malls, peop=
le familiar with the matter said.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In an interview, Larmore said that he planned =
to make all of the required filings related to his purchase of WeWork share=
s and that he couldn=E2=80=99t comment further on the matter until he had d=
one so. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">After the release was issued following the clo=
se of markets, the stock rose briefly.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So, right, they are=C2=A0<em>asking=C2=A0</em>=
about his WeWork trading, and the press release does seem to have moved the=
 stock. On the other hand I don=E2=80=99t know the=C2=A0<em>answers=C2=A0</=
em>about his trading, and if you were going to do this to pump the stock, w=
hy do it after the market closed on a Friday? Bloomberg tells me that WeWor=
k stock closed at $0.8355 that Friday and, uh,=C2=A0reopened the following =
Wednesday, after the bankruptcy filing.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"=
#footnote-3" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bor=
der-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: n=
one !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-b=
lock;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>=C2=A0If you want to manipulate the stock and make a profit, do your pr=
ess release at like 9:31 a.m. on a Monday, so you can trade on it for a bit=
.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: tran=
sparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway I hope he didn=E2=80=99t buy much WeWor=
k stock at $9 per share, as he offered to. That company went bankrupt!</p>
