<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Apparently a lot of the readers of this column=
 are Danish? Or I suppose my readers are just very up on international mort=
gage market structure. Anyway I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/33377885.258417/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMTQvZ29sZG1hbi1rZWVwcy1nZXR0aW5nLW1vcmUtYm9yaW5nP2Nt=
cGlkPUJCRDExMTUyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXd=
zbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMTExNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cB8a4dfcf7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;"> wrote yesterday</a> about the fact that US=
 homeowners have something like $1 trillion of mark-to-market gains on thei=
r mortgages, but that you can=E2=80=99t do anything about it. =E2=80=9CReal=
ly,=E2=80=9D I wrote, =E2=80=9Cthe tempting product is:=E2=80=9D</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You have a $500,000 mortgage that =
is now worth $287,000.<br />You go to your bank and say =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99=
ll give you $300,000 for it.=E2=80=9D<br />The bank is like =E2=80=9Cfine o=
kay that works.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But, I said, you can=E2=80=99t do that: For on=
e thing, your bank probably sold your mortgage; for another thing, this tra=
de would crystallize a big loss for the mortgage owner that it might not ye=
t have booked; for a third thing, US 30-year mortgages don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<=
em>really=C2=A0</em>last 30 years, so no bank would be willing to accept th=
e discounted value of the mortgage cash flows over 30 years.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Quite a lot of readers pointed out that, in De=
nmark, you really can do this. Here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/33377885.258417/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubmV3eW9ya2ZlZC5=
vcmcvbWVkaWFsaWJyYXJ5L21lZGlhL3Jlc2VhcmNoL2Vwci8yMDE4L2Vwcl8yMDE4X3VzLWRhbm=
lzaC1tb3J0Z2FnZS1maW5hbmNlX2JlcmcucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0d3626ab" i=
temprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;"> a New York Fed report</a>, and here is a=C2=A0Carsted=C2=A0Rosenber=
g <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33377885.258417/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuY2Fyc3RlZHJvc2VuYmVyZy5jb20vZGFuaXNoLW1vcnRnYWdlLXN5c3RlbQ/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4884bcc5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> client briefing</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Borrowers may redeem their mortgage loans at a=
ny time without negotiating the price, as prepayment may always take place =
at the prevailing market prices. Danish mortgage borrowers may terminate th=
eir loans by buying back the mortgage bonds in the bond market and deliveri=
ng them to the mortgage bank. This option is referred to as the delivery op=
tion or the buy-back option. The buy-back option applies to all mortgage bo=
nds whether callable or non-callable.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=8BThe buy-back option is a special feat=
ure of the Danish mortgage finance system, and borrowers therefore always k=
now the ISIN code(s) of the bonds behind their mortgage loans. The buy-back=
 option constitutes a significant difference between the US and the Danish =
mortgage finance system. The US system only allows mortgage loan prepayment=
 at par (100).</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Well that=E2=80=99s nice. Obviously if you tra=
nslated this to the US system, and you had a 3% mortgage and rates are now =
8%, you=E2=80=99d be buying back your mortgage at some market price that is=
 lower than par=C2=A0but higher than the value of your mortgage cash flows =
over 30 years discounted at 8%, because the US mortgage market assumes that=
 30-year mortgages have an average life that is much shorter than that. Sti=
ll! You=E2=80=99d get a big discount.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Several other readers emailed me to say some v=
ariation on =E2=80=9CI tried this on my bank but it did not work.=E2=80=9D =
Move to Denmark I guess.</p>
